Subject: convalescence [OGMS:0000091]
Value: A processual entity during which a patient participating in a disease course gradually returns to participating in a canonical life course. @en

Subject: inflammatory process [OGMS:0000095]
Value: A bodily process caused by some disorder that results in recruitment of leukocytes into a localized tissue site, typically causing localized pain and swelling. @en

Subject: remission [OGMS:0000106]
Value: A part of a disease course in which the extent or rate of change of the signs and symptoms of a disorder has decreased. @en

Subject: relapse [OGMS:0000105]
Value: a disease stage which is preceded by a remission and characterized by the return of a manifestation of a disease.

Subject: remission [OGMS:0000106]
Value: a disease stage which is characterized by the lack of a manifestation of a disease.

Subject: physical therapy procedure [OGMS:0000115]
Value: a therapeutic procedure that uses physical conditioning

Subject: asymptomatic [OGMS:0000117]
Value: a disease stage characterized by the lack of symptoms associated with a given disease

Subject: onset [OGMS:0000118]
Value: a disease stage that marks the beginning of a disease

Subject: acute onset [OGMS:0000119]
Value: a disease stage with a rapid unfolding of signs and symptoms

Subject: complete remission [OGMS:0000120]
Value: a remission which is characterized by a prolonged lack of all manifestations of a disease

Subject: partial remission [OGMS:0000121]
Value: a remission which is characterized by a prolonged lack of some manifestations of a disease

Subject: clinical data item [OGMS:0000123]
Value: a data item that is about a patient and is the specified output of a health care process assay or diagnostic process
